00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:38.320
And then we follow it up with Q&amp;A.

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:40.860
It occurs every last Tuesday of the month.

00:03:40.860 --> 00:03:46.480
Today I'm introducing Paola Antonelli, the
senior curator of architecture and design

00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:50.500
here at MoMA, and the director of research
and development.

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:53.340
And she'll be talking about the hoodie.

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:55.560
Thank you, Devin.

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:57.080
It was a great introduction.

00:03:57.080 --> 00:03:58.280
And it's true.

00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:03.980
We pick objects that resonate with us as human
beings, not only as curators.

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:08.700
And more than resonating with me, I live with
this object as we all do.

