So, let me give you first a little bit of
introduction about this exhibition.

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:16.000
You are in an exhibition that, you know, is
called "Items."

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:23.100
And it's about 111 items of clothing that
had a strong impact on a New York-centric

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:25.400
world in the past 100 years.

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:28.240
It is an exhibition about people.

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:34.100
And it's an exhibition about how garments
and fashion interact with people and enable

00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:37.380
people to express themselves and to live in
the world.

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:43.580
So there are many different examples in the
show of everyday items like the white t-shirt,

00:04:43.580 --> 00:04:47.060
like the Levi's 501, or any kind of sneakers.

00:04:47.100 --> 00:04:52.040
And then there are examples of high fashion
from Yves Saint Laurent to Kawakubo all the

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:53.100
way to Armani.

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:55.500
So there's a little bit for everyone.

